Hi all,

Is someone out there working on putting TITLE-ICON SUPOORT in FVWM?(Like
there is in FVWM95)

The reason for asking is because this is what makes the two incompatible
as far as modules.

For example, I have modified FvwmWinList in Fvwm95 to support the Title
Icons, like the TaskBar and added the ability to Reflect what is on your
CURRENT DESK only.  This will not compile on Fvwm2.

If no-one else wants to do this, and no one has big objections to it, I
could maybe do it.



This whole thing leads to the bigger issue of the Fvwm - Fvwm95 split.
Are they really that different that we cannot combine them.  NO.

Here what I see the differences are right now:

Fvwm95 has no corner decorations.  Non issue, Fvwm2 can do this already
(Handle width = 0, Border width = 5)

Fvwm95 has no inner frame shadows, to make it appear like the contents
are seting on some Tile, not inset into something.  I have found where
the inner shadows are in the code, though the outer shadows seam to be
different too.

The only thing that changes colors on Focus is the title bar.
This could some option, or specify the Focused/unfocused title bar
colors separately.

And yes the TITLE-ICONS. These are mini icons that are specified with an
application.  They replace the upper left Window menu button, and are
beside the name in FvwmTaskbar and FvwmWinList(next release).  You can
have mini-icons in Menus too.  In FvwmButtons too eventually.



Ideas, Comments.
Don Mahurin
