>>>>> "DM" == Don Mahurin <dmahurin@donet.com> writes:

DM> This whole thing leads to the bigger issue of the Fvwm - Fvwm95 split.
DM> Are they really that different that we cannot combine them.  NO.

The last thing we need is yet another split.  There have been so many
(Bowman, fvwm95, others I can't remember) and of course fvwm was a split of
its own.  A bunch of diverging development streams just slows down the
whole effort.

Now is of course not the time to try to combine development.  Now is the
time to say "enough with beta versions of fvwm2" and get it out the door.
Chuck is almost ready and we're here to do the testing on various
platforms.

After 2.0 release I think the next thing on the list is the style flag
rewrite.  Once that is finished and debugged it's time to think about
fvwm95 and new features.  I think it's premature to do anything else,
really, until a release is made and the style flags are redone.

The issue of whether or not to incorporate all of those extra goodies is up
to Chuck.  I think that generalizing things like title and border
appearance even further can't hurt and might not bloat things a bit.
Pixmaps in the title bar can't be more complex than the current system,
though I agree with Chuck that it's not fvwm's place to do any kind of
scaling or image manipulation.

