Well, if you allow title-bar buttons to be set on a per-window basis and
the winlist module can get at the buttons then you have the intended
behavior (unless I'm confused about something).  Allowing pixmaps instead
of the current vectorized buttons is just icing on the cake.

I can easily see how having some easy means of identifying what a window
contains would be useful; the icon texts for my xterms contain the current
working directory, not "XTerm".  A little icon besides that would make it a
bit easier when I have twenty windows open.

Jason> I think that generalizing things like title and border appearance
Jason> even further can't hurt and might not bloat things a bit.

