All this talk of pixmaps here and pixmaps there is nice, but it is
very much icing on the cake.

I'd like to present my humble opinion of what the order of things
needing doing should be:

  1) Bug: timing problems with mouse clicks & windows sticking to
              mouse
  2) Docs need going over with fine tooth-comb
  3) Release 2.1.0

  4) Style flags rewrite
  5) Icon placement policy
  6) Module interface (SendToModule?)
  7) finer control over window decorations for fvwm95 people

In particular, 1 is quite serious for people on slow machines (that
includes me).  Chuck, didn't you say you thought you knew what the
problem was?

I have some patches to the manpages that will help with 2 (part of
what I did for the Debian package).

My primary bone of contention is the loss of 1.24r's friendly icon
handling features. I'll have a good think about how to do
user-directed icon placement policy efficiently. I still have my
original patch for this, but it's quite ugly, and is probably in need
of a re-think anyway. If modules can handle two-way communication, it
might be possible for fvwm to use an external module decide the right
place to put an icon down. As I say, this needs thought.

What's currently being discussed is 7 - which in my opinion is quite
far down the list in the priority stakes :)


Austin
