Just wanting to report that the "KillMe" module command patch that I posted a 
while back to the fvwm list definitely solves the fvwm-race-on-tkgoodstuff-rest
arting problem, and to add a plea to incorporate it in the main release.  It 
is very small and I think obviously harmless, and it is a big deal for 
tkgoodstuff, because it allows the user to reconfigure tkgoodstuff and restart 
it without restarting fvwm.  Recall that the problem is that when a module 
leaves children when exiting, fvwm doesn't recognize that it has died, and 
races trying to write to the "full" pipe.  The fix is to let the module tell 
fvwm to kill it, rather than just exiting.  Here is the patch, in case it was 
lost in all my bug-hunting reports:

*** ../fvwm-2.0.42/fvwm/module.c	Tue Apr  2 11:53:31 1996
--- fvwm/module.c	Mon May 27 11:53:28 1996
***************
*** 304,309 ****
--- 304,315 ----
        extern int Context;
        FvwmWindow *tmp_win;
  
+       if(mystrncasecmp(text,"KillMe",6)==0) 
+ 	{
+           KillModule(channel,12);
+           return;
+ 	}
+ 
        /* If a module does XUngrabPointer(), it can now get proper Popups */
        if(mystrncasecmp(text,"popup",5)==0)
  	  Event.xany.type = ButtonPress;

Thanks for considering it!

Cheers,
Mark



