they're extensions)- is to have this ExitFunction:

AddToFunc ExitFunction
+ 	"I"	KillModule FvwmButtons
+	"I"	FvwmBanner
+	"I"	Wait FvwmBanner

where the wait is to make sure, all windows are unswallowed and redisplayed
by the X server, before the restarted new FvwmButton is initializing.
This new FvwmButton would start new copies of all swallowed programs, since
he "can't see" the old ones.

The fix would be for fvwm2 to wait (a little bit more) for the old
FvwmButton module to die, before restarting, and for FvwmButtons to
wait till all unswallowing is finished, before exiting.
This would be a little bit slower on restart, but still faster than the
Quirx with FvwmBanner & wait FvwmBanner in the ExitFunction.

Still, I can see a use for Exitfunction, aside from killing modules.




