Well, um, it's uh, TMLI.  Yeah, TMLI, that's it.  The Tibbs Mailing List
Interface.  Yeah, I like that.  Actually it's the old fashioned tool: the
multi-purpose Swiss army kludge.  The messages are archived into UNIX mbox
folders by archive2.pl, which comes with Majordomo (slightly modified, of
course).  Those folders are processed by MHonArc to generate the indices
and individual message pages.  The backend search engine is Glimpse 3.0
(yes, I know 3.5 is out but this isn't broken so I'm not fixing it).  The
glue that binds this all together is a bunch of perl (5) scripts.  I
actually at one time intended to build in a subscription interface and a
means to reply to messages and then release it, but got caught up in other
things.

