Here is a (merged) patch against plain 2.0.43-almost. It will make
2.0.43 more portable, and fix some bugs.

Followings is the summary of this patch. 'reported:' means that it is
already reported to fvwm-workers@hpc.uh.edu.

* InstallNonExecFile() macro is not defined in X11R4(?)
  (reported: <9606211401.AA23592@vta_host.auto.tuwien.ac.at>)

* 'C++FLAGS' is required for make of BSD/OS 2.x.

* Add 'sgi' defines to configure.h for IRIX, OS specific section.
  (reported: <Pine.OSF.3.91.960623011210.1985K-100000@shorty.csc.umd.edu>>

* extra/FvwmConfig/Imakefile misses 'LOCAL_LIBRARIES' definition.

* extra/FvwmConfig/FvwmDebug.c uses 'waitpid' function.
	Define 'ReapChildrenPid()' macro in extras/FvwmDebug/FvwmDebug.h.
	('ReapChildren()' macro is not suitable to use)

* NEWS-OS 4.x doesn't know pid_t and setvbuf().
	Define these to extras/FvwmDebug/FvwmDebug.h.

* <malloc.h> should NOT use in some OS (maybe warned or error).
	XXX: avoid to include <malloc.h> in extras/FvwmForm2/FvwmForm.c,
	modules/FvwmForm/FvwmForm.c, and modules/FvwmIconMan/FvwmIconMan.h.

* BUGFIX: fvwm/builtin.c uses undefined variable in strerror().
  (reported: <ufaennax9hb.fsf@sina.hpc.uh.edu>)

* BUGFIX: Pixmap alignment incorrect in menu.
  (reported: <9606211527.AA26123@vta_host.auto.tuwien.ac.at>)

* Fix type mismatch warnings.
  (reported: <Pine.OSF.3.91.960623011210.1985K-100000@shorty.csc.umd.edu>)
	See modules/FvwmButtons/FvwmButtons.c, modules/FvwmButtons/parse.c,
	and modules/FvwmTalk/FvwmTalk.c.

* "../../libs/fvwmlib.h" isn't included, though function GetFontOrFixed is used.
	Since function name collision exists, rename CopyString() to
	CopyNString() in modules/FvwmForm/FvwmForm.c.

* Manual typo fix.
	See modules/FvwmForm/FvwmForm.man.

* modules/FvwmIconMan/FvwmIconMan.c uses 'sysconf' function.
	Use 'GetFdWidth' instead.

***

I just compile 2.0.43-almost with this patch successfully, under:
	BSD/OS 2.1 (with NIS patch)/cc (gcc 2.7.2)
	FreeBSD 2.2-960612-SNAP/cc (gcc 2.6.3)
	NEWS-OS 4.2.1a+RD/gcc 2.5.8

Note:
	2.0.43 requires 'cpp should define __DATE__ and __TIME__ macro'.
	Some old-fasioned cpp doesn't define these.

- -
Makoto `MAR_kun' MATSUSHITA

