I  just compared  the  patch that I   submitted for menus  to the left
versus the patch from Lars Wirzenius.

My approach involved tracking the leftmost menu position to avoid ever
having one menu atop another:


                   Menu1 -> Menu 2 --+
                                     |
            Menu3 <------------------+

Lars took the simpler approach of just putting the menu to the left if
there is no room to the right:

                   Menu1 -> Menu 2 --+
                                     |
                   Menu3 <-----------+

So you can end up  with Menu3 obscuring Menu1.  This  turns out not to
be a problem because  you have to  navigate thru Menu2  to get back to
Menu1 anyway.

Everything considered, I like Lars approach much better than mine.

